definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of translational initiation.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of translational initiation.
Any process, mediated by small non-coding RNAs, that modulates the frequency, rate or extent that mRNAs are effectively translated into protein.
Any process, mediated by small non-coding RNAs, that activates or increases the rate that mRNAs are effectively translated into protein.

A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one carbon source leads to the modulation of the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other carbon sources.

A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one carbon source leads to an increase in the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other carbon sources.

label.value: negative regulation of translational initiation by iron

definition.value: Any process involving iron that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of translational initiation.

label.value: positive regulation of translational initiation by iron

definition.value: Any process involving iron that activates or increases the rate of translational initiation.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription by pheromones

definition.value: Any process involving pheromones that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of transcription.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oskar mRNA translation. To ensure the localization of Oskar protein at the posterior pole of the oocyte, translation of oskar mRNA is repressed during its transport to the posterior pole and activated upon localization of the mRNA at the posterior cortex.

label.value: positive regulation of oskar mRNA translation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of oskar mRNA translation.
Any process involving glucose that modulates the frequency, rate or extent or transcription.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription by glucose

definition.value: Any process involving glucose that activates or increases the rate of transcription.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase I promoter, mitotic

definition.value: A cell cycle process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase I promoter during mitosis.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase I promoter during mitosis

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase I promoter during mitosis.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter by pheromones

definition.value: Any process involving pheromones that modulates the frequency, rate or extent or transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter by pheromones

definition.value: Any process involving pheromones that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter, mitotic

definition.value: A cell cycle process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter during mitosis.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter during mitosis

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter during mitosis.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase III promoter, mitotic

definition.value: A cell cycle process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase III promoter during mitosis.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase III promoter during mitosis

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase III promoter during mitosis.
